WEBVTT

00:01.479 --> 00:03.133
- Previously
on "Superman & Lois"...

00:03.177 --> 00:05.135
- Your mom wanted us
to move to Smallville.

00:05.179 --> 00:07.181
- This family needs Smallville.
- I think I did this to him.

00:07.224 --> 00:09.748
The bonfire--I think my heat
vision caused an explosion

00:09.792 --> 00:10.793
and infected him somehow.

00:10.836 --> 00:12.186
Where's Tag now?

00:12.229 --> 00:13.796
- He's with the doctors
at the DOD.

00:13.839 --> 00:16.407
- So what exactly brings
a Reuters tech reporter

00:16.451 --> 00:18.540
to Smallville, Kansas?
- Just want to be on Team Lois.

00:18.583 --> 00:20.281
I think I may have found a way
to get a look inside the mines.

00:20.324 --> 00:21.804
- I don't think it was Derek.

00:21.847 --> 00:23.719
His powers were erratic,
like Tag Harris.

00:23.762 --> 00:25.199
- Well, whatever Edge
and Leslie are doing

00:25.242 --> 00:26.765
with that machine,

00:26.809 --> 00:28.202
it has something to do
with the mines.

00:28.245 --> 00:30.160
- We now own the rights
to this land,

00:30.204 --> 00:32.510
which holds enough X-Kryptonite
to resurrect an army.

00:32.554 --> 00:35.470
[dramatic music]

00:35.513 --> 00:37.776
- Tag.
- What did you do to me?

00:43.826 --> 00:46.263
- Try and outrun me?

00:46.307 --> 00:48.178
Not anymore.

00:48.222 --> 00:50.006
- Tag, I don't know what--

00:50.050 --> 00:52.269
[high-pitched ringing]
[groans]

00:52.313 --> 00:54.445
- [echoing]
I want the truth, Kent.

00:54.489 --> 00:57.100
At the bonfire party,
when you broke my arm,

00:57.144 --> 00:59.102
what did you do to me?

00:59.146 --> 01:02.105
- I don't know what
you're talking about.

01:02.149 --> 01:03.715
- Liar!

01:05.152 --> 01:08.111
Ever since that night,
I have been different.

01:08.155 --> 01:11.506
I can move so fast.
And I saw Teague's video.

01:11.549 --> 01:13.464
Something caused
that explosion.

01:13.508 --> 01:15.988
You were right there.

01:16.032 --> 01:19.166
And I know
you're different, too.

01:19.209 --> 01:22.473
You better tell me
how to fix it.

01:24.693 --> 01:26.738
Superman.
- I'm not gonna hurt you.

01:26.782 --> 01:28.131
Wait!

01:28.175 --> 01:30.699
Are you okay? Are you okay?
- Yeah.

01:44.408 --> 01:46.628
[train horn blows]

01:46.671 --> 01:48.064
Tag, don't!

02:33.240 --> 02:35.024
- He got you pretty good, kid.

02:35.067 --> 02:37.026
- [groans] It's all right.

02:37.069 --> 02:38.419
- Yeah, I thought you had,

02:38.462 --> 02:41.509
like, super durability
or whatever.

02:41.552 --> 02:43.554
- I don't know what I have.

02:43.598 --> 02:48.516
I tried to fight back,
but he was stronger and faster.

02:48.559 --> 02:50.605
My head is pounding.

02:50.648 --> 02:52.563
- Your abilities are evolving.

02:52.607 --> 02:54.478
You can heal faster,
but you can still get hurt.

02:54.522 --> 02:57.351
- What did--what did Tag
want, anyways?

02:57.394 --> 02:59.179
- Answers.

02:59.222 --> 03:00.876
He wanted to know
how he got powers,

03:00.919 --> 03:04.009
why he's at the DOD--
he thinks I did this to him.

03:04.053 --> 03:07.709
- Why would he think that?
- Because he saw the video

03:07.752 --> 03:10.233
of the explosion
I caused at the mines.

03:10.277 --> 03:12.757
I know. Look, he doesn't know
everything,

03:12.801 --> 03:15.934
but he know something's up.

03:15.978 --> 03:18.198
- What if he says something?I mean--

03:18.241 --> 03:20.635
- Guys, can you just give me
and your mom a second

03:20.678 --> 03:23.246
to talk about this, please?

03:25.074 --> 03:28.033
[dramatic music]

03:28.077 --> 03:32.168
♪

03:32.212 --> 03:34.953
- I hate the Internet.
- [chuckles]

03:37.695 --> 03:39.610
- Your dad called.

03:39.654 --> 03:41.699
Assured me that he's on this.

03:41.743 --> 03:44.572
Apparently Tag escaped the DOD
by some fluke.

03:44.615 --> 03:46.008
His abilities accelerated.

03:46.051 --> 03:47.662
They didn't know
what he was capable of.

03:47.705 --> 03:49.446
And now they're putting
together some plan to track him

03:49.490 --> 03:50.621
and get him back in custody.

03:50.665 --> 03:52.362
- And if he gets
to Jordan first?

03:52.406 --> 03:54.190
- I'll keep an eye out.

03:54.234 --> 03:55.931
- This wouldn't be happening
if it wasn't for Morgan Edge.

03:55.974 --> 03:58.934
Whatever gave Tag those powers
came from those mines,

03:58.977 --> 04:00.501
and now he wants
to extract more of it

04:00.544 --> 04:02.894
and make more Derek Powells.

04:02.938 --> 04:04.766
What if you went there?
- I flew over the mines.

04:04.809 --> 04:06.594
I scanned the tunnels.
I can't see inside.

04:06.637 --> 04:08.422
They've lined them
with lead fiber.

04:08.465 --> 04:10.250
- So I need to investigate.

04:10.293 --> 04:12.469
Find proof of wrongdoing,
hand it over

04:12.513 --> 04:14.558
to the authorities,
and get a proper warrant.

04:14.602 --> 04:16.038
- Slow down, okay?
I can find out--

04:16.081 --> 04:17.953
- No, I want you focused
on the boys

04:17.996 --> 04:20.477
until Tag is back in custody.

04:20.521 --> 04:23.306
In the meantime, I got to break
this case open.

04:23.350 --> 04:26.701
Think about it--Edge is giving
people Kryptonian powers.

04:26.744 --> 04:28.703
And all of this
at the same time

04:28.746 --> 04:33.360
some armored lunatic arrives
who knows Superman's real name?

04:33.403 --> 04:37.712
- You think Morgan Edge
is the Stranger?

04:37.755 --> 04:40.715
- Maybe. I don't know.

04:40.758 --> 04:42.107
I'm gonna find out.

04:47.374 --> 04:48.984
- Dude, Jimmy Cutter's
literally been talking

04:49.027 --> 04:51.029
smack about the game all week.

04:51.073 --> 04:52.944
- That guy's such a dick.

04:52.988 --> 04:55.338
- Hey. Hey. Language.

04:56.557 --> 04:58.950
[high-pitched ringing]

04:58.994 --> 05:01.213
You okay?
- Yeah.

05:01.257 --> 05:03.912
Yeah. It's just a headache.
- Hmm.

05:05.217 --> 05:06.958
Jordan, how would you feel

05:07.002 --> 05:10.048
about sitting out
tomorrow's game?

05:10.092 --> 05:11.398
- Why?

05:11.441 --> 05:13.225
- Well, for one,

05:13.269 --> 05:15.489
you might still be affected
by what happened with Tag.

05:15.532 --> 05:17.447
- Well, what does that have
to do with football?

05:17.491 --> 05:19.362
- Yeah, Dad, I mean, look,
it's Metropolis, okay?

05:19.406 --> 05:22.191
This is literally
the biggest game of the season.

05:22.234 --> 05:23.888
It's our old school.
I mean--

05:23.932 --> 05:25.368
- Yeah, I know. I get that,
but until we have this

05:25.412 --> 05:27.283
under control,
we've got to be careful.

05:27.327 --> 05:29.633
- Dad, I have to play
in this game.

05:29.677 --> 05:32.419
It's really important to me.

05:32.462 --> 05:33.724
Please?

05:33.768 --> 05:35.639
- You promise
you're 100% healthy?

05:35.683 --> 05:38.294
- Yeah.
- Totally good to go?

05:38.338 --> 05:41.341
- Totally good to go.
- Okay. All right.

05:41.384 --> 05:44.648
Then after school,
you're gonna prove it.

05:44.692 --> 05:47.912
- This is proof my suspicions
were correct.

05:47.956 --> 05:50.567
Smallville is the community
that's going to help me

05:50.611 --> 05:52.743
change the world.

05:52.787 --> 05:54.223
So, without further ado,

05:54.266 --> 05:56.007
I'll hand over
to my wonderful staff,

05:56.051 --> 05:59.141
who can assist in getting you
all back to work.

05:59.184 --> 06:00.708
- Yeah.
- Thank you very much.

06:00.751 --> 06:03.580
- Yeah.
[chuckles]

06:03.624 --> 06:05.408
Oh, Mr. Edge,

06:05.452 --> 06:08.106
this is gonna put a lot
of people back on their feet.

06:08.150 --> 06:09.804
I cannot thank you enough.

06:09.847 --> 06:11.849
- No, no, I'm the one
who should be thanking you.

06:11.893 --> 06:15.070
All this is possible
because of your advocacy,

06:15.113 --> 06:17.420
persuading people
to give me a shot.

06:17.464 --> 06:20.989
In fact, I'd like
to capitalize on our momentum.

06:21.032 --> 06:22.904
- Hey, whatever you need,
you say the word.

06:22.947 --> 06:25.950
- Well, the Smallville team
needs a strong leader.

06:25.994 --> 06:28.953
And I'd like to fill
that role with you, Lana.

06:31.478 --> 06:33.088
- With me?
- The work you did at the bank

06:33.131 --> 06:34.611
with reverse mortgages

06:34.655 --> 06:37.222
shows me you're not
just highly competent.

06:37.266 --> 06:39.442
You also have
the people's trust.

06:39.486 --> 06:43.054
And I want to use that trust
to revitalize Smallville,

06:43.098 --> 06:46.231
starting with
the community center.

06:46.275 --> 06:49.278
- Yeah.
- I'm grateful.

06:49.321 --> 06:52.673
[chuckles]
I-I don't know what to say.

06:52.716 --> 06:55.763
- Well, when you see
your new starting salary,

06:55.806 --> 06:58.287
you'll say yes.
- [chuckles]

06:58.330 --> 07:01.290
[dramatic music]

07:01.333 --> 07:08.079
♪

07:08.123 --> 07:11.692
- Should I deal with her?
- Why bother?

07:11.735 --> 07:14.390
What can she do?

07:14.434 --> 07:17.437
[indistinct chatter]

07:21.702 --> 07:23.834
- Figured out how to get
in there yet?

07:23.878 --> 07:25.749
- Doing about as well
as you, Marcus.

07:27.925 --> 07:30.319
- May the best reporter in.

07:30.362 --> 07:32.016
- Uh, he's just worried
about you man.

07:32.060 --> 07:33.496
You need to cut Dad
a little slack.

07:33.540 --> 07:35.498
- I know he's just
looking out for me,

07:35.542 --> 07:39.110
but he thinks I'm made
of glass.

07:39.154 --> 07:40.677
This is my shot to finally show

07:40.721 --> 07:42.331
those Metropolis d-bags
who's boss.

07:42.374 --> 07:45.508
Come on.
I'm not gonna sit that out.

07:45.552 --> 07:47.945
- I get that.
But I'm just saying--what?

07:47.989 --> 07:49.947
- You don't have to
slam it every time.

07:49.991 --> 07:51.601
- Dude, I didn't even
slam it at all.

07:51.645 --> 07:52.950
- Oh, hey, guys.

07:52.994 --> 07:54.561
Oh, my God,
what happened to your face?

07:54.604 --> 07:56.214
- Um...

07:56.258 --> 07:59.130
- Did you get beat up
on your way home or something?

07:59.174 --> 08:01.089
- We were running plays this
morning in the front yard,

08:01.132 --> 08:03.134
and then I juked him,
and he tripped and fell.

08:03.178 --> 08:04.962
- Well, I hope you do better
tomorrow at the game,

08:05.006 --> 08:06.529
'cause I'd hate to go
all the way to Metropolis

08:06.573 --> 08:08.052
just to see you eat it.

08:08.096 --> 08:09.880
- You're coming?
- Uh, yeah.

08:09.924 --> 08:12.796
Friends can root
for friends, right?

08:15.277 --> 08:16.713
- I think I'm starting to see

08:16.757 --> 08:18.585
why you're so hyped
for this game, huh?

08:18.628 --> 08:20.325
[school bell ringing]
- [groans]

08:20.369 --> 08:22.589
- What?
Hey, hey, hey, Jordan, Jordan.

08:22.632 --> 08:25.156
[echoing] What's going on?
Hey. Hey.

08:25.200 --> 08:27.898
[continues indistinctly]

08:32.076 --> 08:34.731
- Jordan. Jordan.
Look at me, look at me.

08:34.775 --> 08:37.734
Just breathe. Just breathe.
Please, just breathe.

08:37.778 --> 08:39.954
- [breathing heavily]

08:39.997 --> 08:42.870
- Hey. Hey.
What the hell was that?

08:42.913 --> 08:46.134
Okay, that is not--
that is not a panic attack.

08:46.177 --> 08:47.962
- It's my head.

08:48.005 --> 08:49.746
Since Tag jumped me,

08:49.790 --> 08:53.184
I've been hearing this
really loud high-pitched noise.

08:53.228 --> 08:56.971
- Jordan, if this has to do
with your superpowers,

08:57.014 --> 08:58.886
then you need to tell Dad.

08:58.929 --> 09:00.409
You might need to go
to the fortress

09:00.452 --> 09:02.411
to figure out what's wrong.

09:02.454 --> 09:04.152
- We can't tell Dad, all right?
- Jordan, you need to tell him.

09:04.195 --> 09:05.632
- Look, if we tell Dad,

09:05.675 --> 09:06.850
he won't let me play football
tomorrow.

09:06.894 --> 09:10.201
- Jordan.
- Jon, let me have this.

09:10.245 --> 09:12.987
Those Metropolis guys--Woodrum,
Cutter, Campana--

09:13.030 --> 09:15.511
they've made my life hell.

09:15.555 --> 09:20.081
Just let me shut them up,
just this once.

09:24.041 --> 09:25.652
- All right, bye.

09:25.695 --> 09:30.613
It's Bill Hastings.
He starts work next week.

09:30.657 --> 09:33.573
Hadn't heard him this excited
since Junior was born.

09:33.616 --> 09:36.097
- You're changing lives, babe.

09:36.140 --> 09:37.620
- Yeah.

09:37.664 --> 09:40.014
- Hey. You okay?

09:40.057 --> 09:41.493
- Yeah.

09:45.062 --> 09:48.805
It's silly, but I don't know,
I just--I thought

09:48.849 --> 09:53.027
that Edge might have
had something for me, you know?

09:53.070 --> 09:54.898
Some managerial work
or something like that.

09:54.942 --> 09:57.248
- I know.
But do you really want that?

09:57.292 --> 10:00.425
I mean,
you love being a fireman,

10:00.469 --> 10:02.036
and if I'm getting
this promotion,

10:02.079 --> 10:03.777
isn't
that a win for both of us?

10:05.300 --> 10:07.128
[doorbell rings]

10:07.171 --> 10:10.697
- I'll be right back, baby.
[door opens]

10:11.698 --> 10:14.657
Lois. Let me go grab Lana.

10:14.701 --> 10:19.488
- Actually, Kyle, I was hoping
that I could talk to you, too.

10:19.531 --> 10:21.185
- Come on in.

10:21.229 --> 10:24.275
- This may sound bizarre,
but I have reason to believe

10:24.319 --> 10:26.060
that Morgan Edge is engaged

10:26.103 --> 10:28.628
in both illegal
and dangerous activity,

10:28.671 --> 10:30.586
and I'm asking for your help
to get into the mines

10:30.630 --> 10:32.109
so that I can prove it.

10:32.153 --> 10:33.763
- So let me get this straight.

10:33.807 --> 10:36.157
Even though Edge just gave Lana
this massive promotion,

10:36.200 --> 10:37.854
you want us
to go behind his back

10:37.898 --> 10:40.422
and help you with a news story.

10:40.465 --> 10:43.468
- I know it's a big ask.
- It's pretty big, yeah.

10:45.253 --> 10:47.559
- Listen, I'm not alone
in my suspicions.

10:47.603 --> 10:49.039
You both know
that I know Superman.

10:49.083 --> 10:50.737
He's looking into Edge, too.

10:50.780 --> 10:54.349
- Superman? What for?
- I can't tell you that yet.

10:54.392 --> 10:55.959
- Of course you can't.

10:56.003 --> 10:57.831
- But does Clark know
about this?

10:57.874 --> 11:00.877
- He doesn't know I'm here, no.
I'm just trying to explain--

11:00.921 --> 11:02.226
- Explain what?

11:02.270 --> 11:04.141
You've got no proof.
You got no evidence.

11:04.185 --> 11:06.143
- Kyle, I would tell you
if I could.

11:06.187 --> 11:08.102
I am asking you to trust me.

11:08.145 --> 11:10.582
- Oh, okay, you want me
to trust you?

11:10.626 --> 11:12.019
You know what I should do
is, I should call Edge

11:12.062 --> 11:13.411
and we should get
a restraining order.

11:13.455 --> 11:15.283
- Okay, Kyle, please.

11:15.326 --> 11:18.025
- Listen, I just got off
the phone with a buddy of mine

11:18.068 --> 11:21.071
who hadn't worked
in eight months.

11:21.115 --> 11:23.726
He's got mouths to feed, Lois.

11:23.770 --> 11:25.728
And right now
Edge is the only person

11:25.772 --> 11:27.904
that's giving his family
a chance to survive.

11:27.948 --> 11:29.863
- I know it seems like
he's helping,

11:29.906 --> 11:33.344
but he has--
- No, he is helping...

11:33.388 --> 11:35.651
a lot more than you are.

11:38.872 --> 11:41.483
- I came to you guys
because you're my friends

11:41.526 --> 11:43.093
and I need help.

11:43.137 --> 11:46.401
- I know I maybe be biased,
but you don't know

11:46.444 --> 11:49.012
what it's like
to see this town dry up.

11:49.056 --> 11:52.581
The things I've see--
foreclosing on people--

11:52.624 --> 11:55.453
this is our chance to help.

11:57.891 --> 12:00.328
I'm sorry, Lois.

12:04.593 --> 12:07.117
- Lana, you know
that I respect you.

12:07.161 --> 12:10.425
So I am telling you, something
sinister is going on here.

12:10.468 --> 12:14.255
And you might not find out
what it is until it's too late.

12:14.298 --> 12:16.387
So just be careful.

12:16.431 --> 12:19.390
[dramatic music]

12:19.434 --> 12:22.393
♪

12:22.437 --> 12:24.656
- [sighs]

12:24.700 --> 12:27.964
- So why are we down here?
- Training.

12:28.008 --> 12:29.923
This is stuff your grandfather
used to teach me

12:29.966 --> 12:31.794
how to control my strength.

12:31.838 --> 12:33.796
Now it's my turn
to give you a few pointers.

12:33.840 --> 12:36.277
- Why, so he can, like, protect
himself from Tag or something?

12:36.320 --> 12:39.062
- Well, there's that,
and given your raw power,

12:39.106 --> 12:41.325
we want to make sure
you can control it.

12:41.369 --> 12:45.025
- Yeah, I mean, a random super
freak-out would really suck.

12:45.068 --> 12:47.723
- Yeah.
Anyway...

12:47.767 --> 12:50.857
let's start with this.

12:50.900 --> 12:53.511
- Am I somehow supposed
to crack this in half?

12:53.555 --> 12:56.210
- Nope. Just punch it.

12:56.253 --> 12:58.429
- Don't I need gloves
or something?

12:58.473 --> 12:59.996
- You trust me?

13:04.435 --> 13:05.959
- [mutters]

13:10.093 --> 13:11.486
Ouch.

13:11.529 --> 13:12.966
- Thanks, Dad.
- Yep. Yep. Okay.

13:13.009 --> 13:14.532
No, I thought we'd try
going on instinct,

13:14.576 --> 13:16.143
but obviously that was
the wrong approach.

13:16.186 --> 13:17.971
Um, right foot back.
Put your hand up like a fist.

13:18.014 --> 13:22.497
Curl your thumb. Bring it back.
Transfer the weight.

13:22.540 --> 13:23.759
Follow through.

13:23.803 --> 13:25.500
- Okay.

13:25.543 --> 13:27.981
- Jordan...

13:28.024 --> 13:32.724
imagine--imagine this big log
is Cutter's face.

13:32.768 --> 13:36.859
He's just laughing at you.
Pop him. You got it.

13:36.903 --> 13:38.861
- Come on, believe you can do
this, and you will.

13:38.905 --> 13:40.863
You're stronger than
you think you are.

13:40.907 --> 13:42.212
- You got it.
- Now.

13:43.823 --> 13:46.826
Yes! Yes!

13:46.869 --> 13:48.828
- Yo, that's what
I'm talking about!

13:48.871 --> 13:52.179
Yes, sir. Oh, my God.
- See? Line it up again.

13:52.222 --> 13:53.920
Line it up again.
- Okay. Okay. Okay. Okay.

13:53.963 --> 13:55.617
[cell phone rings]
- Hold on. Hold on. Wait. Wait.

13:55.660 --> 13:57.184
Hang on, hang on.
- Okay.

13:57.227 --> 13:58.576
Hey, Sam.

13:58.620 --> 14:00.491
- Harris was spotted
in Metropolis.

14:00.535 --> 14:02.711
- In Metropolis?
Are you sure?

14:02.754 --> 14:05.235
- He's fast, hard to track.

14:05.279 --> 14:07.629
Why?
Something I need to know about?

14:07.672 --> 14:11.285
- Uh, that's where the boys'
football game is tomorrow.

14:11.328 --> 14:13.635
- You stay with the boys.
I'll have my guys on site.

14:13.678 --> 14:16.899
We have a plan to put this
monster back in his cage.

14:16.943 --> 14:18.901
- He's not a monster, Sam.
He's a kid.

14:18.945 --> 14:20.424
Nobody's helping him.
He's scared.

14:20.468 --> 14:23.906
- Helping?
He attacked my grandson.

14:23.950 --> 14:26.909
No, I underestimated him once.

14:26.953 --> 14:29.651
He broke out
of a state-of-the-art facility.

14:29.694 --> 14:31.044
His speed rivals yours.

14:31.087 --> 14:33.089
No telling what damage
he can do.

14:33.133 --> 14:34.743
I don't have time to worry
about feelings.

14:34.786 --> 14:36.527
I need to incapacitate
a threat.

14:36.571 --> 14:38.094
That's what I'm gonna do.

14:38.138 --> 14:41.010
[line clicks]

14:41.054 --> 14:42.925
- Getting a sitter?

14:42.969 --> 14:44.927
- I'm trying.

14:44.971 --> 14:48.844
But nobody we know
is available for tomorrow.

14:48.888 --> 14:50.193
- What's tomorrow?

14:50.237 --> 14:51.978
- Your dad's
taking me to dinner.

14:52.021 --> 14:54.110
We're celebrating
my new promotion.

14:54.154 --> 14:56.286
- [scoffs]
Wow.

14:56.330 --> 14:58.636
Dad finally got over
himself long enough to think,

14:58.680 --> 15:02.858
"Maybe I should
congratulate my wife."

15:02.902 --> 15:05.905
- Were you listening
to our conversation?

15:05.948 --> 15:09.299
- It's not that big of a house.

15:09.343 --> 15:11.345
- Sarah...

15:11.388 --> 15:15.001
your dad--he's trying.

15:21.181 --> 15:23.487
- [sighs]
I can watch Sophie.

15:25.489 --> 15:29.232
- But what about the game?
- There's other games.

15:29.276 --> 15:31.278
- Sarah.
- Mom.

15:31.321 --> 15:33.497
Your new job, it's kind of,
like, a really big deal,

15:33.541 --> 15:37.458
and you absolutely deserve
to go and celebrate.

15:39.242 --> 15:40.983
- I guess.

15:41.027 --> 15:43.159
I guess it's a big deal.

15:43.203 --> 15:45.205
- Yeah. You work really hard.

15:45.248 --> 15:47.250
And you give back
to the community.

15:47.294 --> 15:50.514
So you do deserve
all the karma you're getting.

15:51.733 --> 15:53.474
- Mm.

15:54.866 --> 15:58.914
Who knows? Maybe--maybe this
is just the start.

16:04.180 --> 16:07.140
[sinister music]

16:07.183 --> 16:12.710
♪

16:16.018 --> 16:17.324
- Come on, now!

16:17.367 --> 16:18.368
- We are now
in the second quarter

16:18.412 --> 16:21.110
of a surprisingly close game.

16:21.154 --> 16:23.504
- There's no show in showtime
if we don't show up!

16:23.547 --> 16:26.507
- Hey. You okay?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

16:26.550 --> 16:30.685
- Hey, short stack, you see
that linebacker, 55, out there?

16:30.728 --> 16:32.078
He's been killing us all day.

16:32.121 --> 16:33.775
Now, look,
I want you to go in there

16:33.818 --> 16:37.039
and you knock him
on his backside, you got that?

16:37.083 --> 16:40.782
Let's go. Let's go!
[crowd cheering]

16:40.825 --> 16:45.439
- Gonna stick your ass, Jo-Jo.
Just like grade school.

16:45.482 --> 16:47.702
[whistle blows]

16:47.745 --> 16:50.705
- [groans]
[high-pitched ringing]

16:50.748 --> 16:54.187
- Here we go.
Keep them out!

16:54.230 --> 16:56.928
Come on, now! Jeez!

16:56.972 --> 17:01.759
- Oh! Looks like the Crows'
quarterback is hurt.

17:05.111 --> 17:06.851
- Timmy's got
a sprained elbow.

17:06.895 --> 17:08.723
Tried telling Jordan
it's not really his fault.

17:08.766 --> 17:10.594
- [chuckles]
Yeah, I'm sure that helped.

17:10.638 --> 17:12.901
What about our other problem?
Any sign of our friend Tag?

17:12.944 --> 17:15.425
- No. There's a pretty big
DOD presence.

17:15.469 --> 17:17.079
Guess I should thank
your dad for that.

17:17.123 --> 17:18.907
- Well, the sooner
we find that kid,

17:18.950 --> 17:20.474
the sooner this
will all be over.

17:20.517 --> 17:23.216
- Yeah.
It's the how that worries me.

17:23.259 --> 17:25.261
- Clark, with everything
that's going on,

17:25.305 --> 17:27.263
are you sure Jordan's okay?

17:27.307 --> 17:28.960
- I don't know.

17:29.004 --> 17:31.093
Something's going on,
but he won't talk to me.

17:31.137 --> 17:33.269
- Keep an eye on him,
on both of them.

17:33.313 --> 17:35.271
This can't be easy for them,
playing their old school

17:35.315 --> 17:37.491
and seeing
all the kids they knew.

17:37.534 --> 17:38.927
- Yeah.

17:38.970 --> 17:41.408
[whistle blows]
- Hut!

17:41.451 --> 17:43.323
- Come on!

17:43.366 --> 17:45.586
We got to do our job!
Pick it up now!

17:45.629 --> 17:46.935
Let's go!
Focus!

17:46.978 --> 17:49.546
- Coach.
We need to throw that ball.

17:49.590 --> 17:51.374
- I don't got
a quarterback, Kent.

17:51.418 --> 17:53.159
- You do, Coach.
You got me.

17:53.202 --> 17:55.074
I mean, I know our plays.

17:55.117 --> 17:59.904
I know their defense.
I got this, okay?

17:59.948 --> 18:01.471
- All right, Kent.

18:01.515 --> 18:04.257
Strong right slot,
Z panther, on three.

18:04.300 --> 18:05.867
- Got it.
- Let's go!

18:05.910 --> 18:07.434
- Go get them, 12.

18:07.477 --> 18:09.566
- What a game
this has been so far.

18:09.610 --> 18:11.046
There is no love lost
between these two teams.

18:11.090 --> 18:12.743
- Whoo-hoo. Big boy Kent.

18:12.787 --> 18:15.616
Hey, you know I'm with your
girl Eliza now, right?

18:15.659 --> 18:17.661
She wanted you to know.

18:17.705 --> 18:20.055
- Blue 72. Hike!

18:24.190 --> 18:27.367
- Ball, ball, ball!

18:27.410 --> 18:30.587
- Touchdown, Smallville.
- Yeah! Attaboy!

18:30.631 --> 18:33.982
- You like that, Cutter?

18:34.025 --> 18:35.549
- Hey. Jordan.

18:35.592 --> 18:36.985
Get over here.

18:39.161 --> 18:42.164
Rein it in, or you're done.
- Just making a block.

18:42.208 --> 18:44.471
- That's not what I'm talking
about, and you know it.

18:44.514 --> 18:46.037
You understand me?

18:46.081 --> 18:48.823
- Yeah.
- Good. Go sit down.

18:50.303 --> 18:52.957
- Hell, use me
as your unnamed source.

18:53.001 --> 18:55.656
All I need is a press pass
from the "Post."

18:55.699 --> 18:58.876
[knock at door]
I'll call you back.

18:58.920 --> 19:01.792
No, I'm not mad.
Just find me a pass.

19:01.836 --> 19:04.795
[dramatic music]

19:04.839 --> 19:11.846
♪

19:13.630 --> 19:15.110
[knock at door]

19:15.154 --> 19:16.981
Who is it?

19:17.025 --> 19:19.114
- Your new best friend.

19:23.727 --> 19:26.077
- What are you
doing here, Marcus?

19:26.121 --> 19:28.384
- Still open to sharing
a byline?

19:28.428 --> 19:31.474
Friend of mine got hands
on a couple inspector badges.

19:31.518 --> 19:35.174
One's for you, if you want it.

19:35.217 --> 19:37.567
- You somehow get not one
but two inspector badges

19:37.611 --> 19:40.048
and you're just gonna give me
one of them to be nice?

19:42.616 --> 19:45.619
- They're working around the
clock to get those mines ready.

19:45.662 --> 19:48.448
Right now the tunnels
are packed with inspectors.

19:48.491 --> 19:50.972
Security is stretched thin.

19:51.015 --> 19:53.235
A lone Black guy
might look suspicious,

19:53.279 --> 19:56.238
but the two of us together,
it'll seem more legit.

19:56.282 --> 19:57.892
So...

19:57.935 --> 19:59.676
are you in...

19:59.720 --> 20:01.765
or out?

20:01.809 --> 20:03.245
- Are you kidding me?

20:03.289 --> 20:05.073
This is your idea
of a disguise?

20:05.116 --> 20:07.075
It's kind of a clown show.
- Let me do the talking, okay?

20:07.118 --> 20:09.556
You just try
to look inspector-y.

20:09.599 --> 20:12.994
- Inspector-y.
- Mine Safety.

20:13.037 --> 20:14.909
- That team checked
in hours ago.

20:14.952 --> 20:16.476
- Had to grab more equipment.

20:16.519 --> 20:20.828
Dude, between you and me,
Sullivan is an idiot.

20:20.871 --> 20:23.352
[both laugh]
He can't plan a survey.

20:23.396 --> 20:25.572
- All right, go ahead.
- All right, cool. Thanks, man.

20:25.615 --> 20:27.878
[chuckles]

20:27.922 --> 20:30.446
- You want to watch a classic?
There's "Wizard of Oz."

20:30.490 --> 20:32.056
- But I like animation.

20:32.100 --> 20:34.320
We can get a new one
on streaming.

20:34.363 --> 20:36.626
- No, I'm not gonna buy--
look, Soph,

20:36.670 --> 20:39.455
I'm fine with the whole, like,
Saturday sister bonding time.

20:39.499 --> 20:41.022
Kind of embrace it.

20:41.065 --> 20:42.458
But, dude, seriously,
we're gonna have to find

20:42.502 --> 20:43.981
something
we both want to watch.

20:44.025 --> 20:46.332
- Please?

20:46.375 --> 20:48.290
[doorbell rings]
- Okay, that's the pizza guy.

20:48.334 --> 20:49.639
Get up.

20:50.988 --> 20:53.252
Okay, go get your stuffies
and your blankets,

20:53.295 --> 20:54.644
and then you can pick
whatever movie you want.

20:54.688 --> 20:56.298
Just--

20:56.342 --> 20:58.996
I'll be back after I'm done
emotionally preparing.

21:01.172 --> 21:02.478
Love you, too.

21:02.522 --> 21:05.133
- Love you.
- Little brat.

21:05.176 --> 21:07.701
[sighs]

21:07.744 --> 21:09.746
Tag.
- Hey, Sarah.

21:09.790 --> 21:11.357
- Thought you went to go live
with your dad.

21:11.400 --> 21:13.097
Are you back in town?

21:13.141 --> 21:17.145
- The truth is complicated.

21:17.188 --> 21:19.495
And you've always been
my friend.

21:19.539 --> 21:23.325
You stick up for people when
you know something isn't fair.

21:23.369 --> 21:24.979
- No!

21:27.895 --> 21:29.810
- Sarah. Sarah.

21:32.421 --> 21:35.337
- The Crows lead 35-13
in the fourth quarter,

21:35.381 --> 21:37.513
with only seconds left
on the clock.

21:37.557 --> 21:40.951
Nobody saw this coming, least
of all the Metropolis players.

21:40.995 --> 21:42.866
They look absolutely stunned.

21:42.910 --> 21:45.739
- Blue, 72. Hut. Hut. Hike!

21:50.309 --> 21:51.875
- Go! Go!
- Whoo!

21:51.919 --> 21:53.137
- Touchdown, Crows!

21:53.181 --> 21:54.487
- Yeah! Attaboy!

21:54.530 --> 21:56.750
- The Crows win.
What an upset!

21:56.793 --> 21:58.447
- [groaning]

21:58.491 --> 22:00.536
- Looks like a fight
has broken out midfield.

22:00.580 --> 22:02.190
I don't think
I've ever seen

22:02.233 --> 22:04.453
anything like this!
- Whoa. Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.

22:06.586 --> 22:08.544
- Get off him!

22:11.852 --> 22:13.462
- Hey. Hey. Jordan, you okay?

22:13.506 --> 22:15.812
- I can't hold it in.

22:15.856 --> 22:18.380
- Let it out.
Let it out right now.

22:18.424 --> 22:22.297
- [screaming]

22:29.043 --> 22:31.741
- I had a really
good time tonight.

22:31.785 --> 22:33.221
- Well, good,

22:33.264 --> 22:36.006
'cause that dinner
wasn't cheap.

22:36.050 --> 22:39.314
[both chuckle]

22:39.358 --> 22:42.012
- Listen, um...

22:42.056 --> 22:45.842
we didn't talk about logistics,
with my new hours,

22:45.886 --> 22:48.889
how that might affect the kids
or how you feel about it.

22:48.932 --> 22:51.108
- Whatever we got to do,
we're gonna do, okay?

22:51.152 --> 22:54.242
- I know. But--
- No. There's no buts.

22:54.285 --> 22:58.420
Yeah, maybe I'm a little
disappointed, but it's fine.

22:58.464 --> 23:02.250
- You saw Morgan Edge
as an opportunity

23:02.293 --> 23:04.208
before anybody.

23:04.252 --> 23:07.037
Of course you should be
rewarded for that.

23:07.081 --> 23:09.126
He's an idiot
if he can't see that.

23:09.170 --> 23:12.869
- Whoa, whoa, he is not
an idiot, okay?

23:12.913 --> 23:15.829
He promoted you,
after all, right?

23:15.872 --> 23:17.570
[chuckles]

23:17.613 --> 23:21.487
Listen, babe, you got to know
I'm real proud of you.

23:21.530 --> 23:24.403
I mean, you are the brains
of this family, after all.

23:24.446 --> 23:26.056
We all know that.

23:26.100 --> 23:29.799
[chuckles]
You deserve to be happy.

23:29.843 --> 23:32.541
- I'm happy.
- Well, good.

23:32.585 --> 23:35.501
Then whatever comes next,

23:35.544 --> 23:38.460
I think we will handle it...

23:38.504 --> 23:41.594
- Mm-hmm.
- Together.

23:41.637 --> 23:44.510
- Did you get me desert?

23:44.553 --> 23:47.556
- Oh, sweets,
it's way past your bedtime.

23:47.600 --> 23:50.994
- Where is your sister?
- I think she's in her room.

23:52.213 --> 23:54.302
- Yeah. Go check.

23:54.345 --> 23:55.390
Come here.

23:55.434 --> 23:58.306
[suspenseful music]

23:58.349 --> 23:59.829
♪

23:59.873 --> 24:02.963
- No.

24:03.006 --> 24:05.400
- It's not like Sarah
to just leave.

24:05.444 --> 24:08.011
- I'm gonna check
the security cam footage.

24:08.055 --> 24:10.797
- For the hundredth time,
I'm fine.

24:10.840 --> 24:12.712
- No, you're not.

24:12.755 --> 24:14.322
You just detonated like a bomb

24:14.365 --> 24:15.715
in the middle of a high-school
football game

24:15.758 --> 24:17.238
in front of a crowd
full of people.

24:17.281 --> 24:18.631
- I could have controlled it,
all right?

24:18.674 --> 24:20.546
I just let it go
'cause you were there.

24:20.589 --> 24:23.113
- Yeah, but what if I wasn't?

24:23.157 --> 24:25.768
Jordan, sit up and look at me.

24:28.292 --> 24:31.774
Do you understand
how dangerous this could be?

24:31.818 --> 24:33.428
Tell me exactly what happened.

24:33.472 --> 24:35.996
Were there--were there
any symptoms, any signs,

24:36.039 --> 24:38.389
something that would have made
you think that this was coming?

24:38.433 --> 24:39.652
- Look, Dad, you're thinking
about this too much.

24:39.695 --> 24:41.871
I just--I had a moment,
all right?

24:41.915 --> 24:45.919
- Jordan...
that's not 100% true.

24:45.962 --> 24:47.268
- Jon.
- What?

24:47.311 --> 24:48.965
- Jordan, he needs to know.

24:49.009 --> 24:51.968
Look, the first time that he
had one of these episodes

24:52.012 --> 24:53.927
or whatever,
I mean, it stopped.

24:53.970 --> 24:56.277
It seemed fine.

24:56.320 --> 24:58.932
- The first time?
- I had a migraine at school.

24:58.975 --> 25:01.325
It wasn't a big deal.
- And you didn't tell me?

25:01.369 --> 25:03.545
- I didn't tell you
'cause I knew you'd overreact.

25:03.589 --> 25:04.981
I knew you'd stop me
from playing the game.

25:05.025 --> 25:06.548
- Yeah!
And I would have been right!

25:06.592 --> 25:07.854
- So I'm just supposed
to be punished

25:07.897 --> 25:09.899
for something
that isn't my fault?

25:09.943 --> 25:11.771
This was my shot, Dad.

25:11.814 --> 25:16.123
This was my chance to show the
d-bags at Metropolis who I am.

25:16.166 --> 25:18.908
You remember
how they treated me, right?

25:18.952 --> 25:21.171
- Jordan, I know. I know.
And I get it, okay?

25:21.215 --> 25:22.956
I know what it's like
to be picked on.

25:22.999 --> 25:25.654
- Yeah, but you get to grow up,
and you get to be Superman.

25:25.698 --> 25:28.178
Who am I?

25:28.222 --> 25:30.964
I'm a weird kid with headaches.

25:32.574 --> 25:36.578
I just--I wanted to be good
at something--that was all.

25:36.622 --> 25:39.102
- That's not what
your powers are for. Jordan--

25:39.146 --> 25:43.324
- Dad, I'm not you, okay?

25:43.367 --> 25:46.370
[sighs]

25:49.417 --> 25:51.419
[cell phone ringing]

25:51.462 --> 25:53.464
- Hey, Lana, sorry.
Can I--can I call you back?

25:53.508 --> 25:56.119
- Clark, real quick--
did Sarah come to the game?

25:56.163 --> 25:59.949
- Uh...no, I didn't see her.
Why? Is everything okay?

25:59.993 --> 26:02.038
- Well, she was supposed
to be here with Sophie,

26:02.082 --> 26:03.823
and she's not.

26:03.866 --> 26:05.389
I knew she'd canceled plans
about coming to the game.

26:05.433 --> 26:07.043
I just thought--

26:07.087 --> 26:09.872
- Is that that Harris kid?
- Oh, my God, yeah it is.

26:09.916 --> 26:12.614
- Clark, I got to go.
[line clicks]

26:12.658 --> 26:14.573
- What was that?
- Stay here.

26:14.616 --> 26:17.445
- Everything okay?
- Stay here.

26:17.488 --> 26:19.012
- You sure about this?

26:19.055 --> 26:21.449
- No point playing it cautious
now, right?

26:21.492 --> 26:23.016
- And you know
what to look for?

26:23.059 --> 26:25.627
- Yeah. Got my hands
on some schematics.

26:25.671 --> 26:28.761
What we want is just up ahead.

26:28.804 --> 26:33.026
- And how, may I ask, did you
manage to just take a peak

26:33.069 --> 26:36.203
at Edge EnerCorp's
top secret schematics?

26:36.246 --> 26:38.640
- Uh, friend of mine helped out

26:38.684 --> 26:41.034
with some surgically
precise hacking.

26:41.077 --> 26:43.079
- Well, points to you
and your friend.

26:43.123 --> 26:45.647
And the grand prize is...

26:45.691 --> 26:48.345
- Should be right here.
Yeah.

26:52.436 --> 26:54.569
- You came prepared.

27:00.531 --> 27:02.751
[distant siren wailing]

27:17.244 --> 27:21.291
- Tag, what the hell?
Where are we?

27:21.335 --> 27:25.513
- It's okay.
We're in Metropolis.

27:25.556 --> 27:28.690
- How are we in Metropolis?

27:28.734 --> 27:30.866
- That's the thing, Sarah.

27:30.910 --> 27:34.043
I can move pretty fast now.

27:34.087 --> 27:36.829
[mysterious music]

27:36.872 --> 27:41.181
♪

27:41.224 --> 27:44.097
- So a high-tech gadget guy
works for LuthorCorps,

27:44.140 --> 27:46.012
the top tech company
in the world,

27:46.055 --> 27:50.712
only to quit and pursue
a career in journalism.

27:50.756 --> 27:52.714
Did I get that right?

27:52.758 --> 27:55.630
Feels like I should be focusing
my story on you.

28:03.029 --> 28:04.900
- No, the, uh...

28:04.944 --> 28:08.121
story...

28:08.164 --> 28:10.210
is on what's in these walls.

28:10.253 --> 28:11.515
- What is that?

28:11.559 --> 28:15.606
- X-K, otherwise known
as X-Kryptonite.

28:15.650 --> 28:17.304
- X-Kryptonite?

28:17.347 --> 28:19.349
- Rarest form of Kryptonite.

28:19.393 --> 28:21.482
And if my hunch is right,

28:21.525 --> 28:24.746
these mines have the largest
supply of it anywhere.

28:24.790 --> 28:26.400
There's your story, Miss Lane.

28:26.443 --> 28:28.402
- Too bad no one's
gonna read it.

28:28.445 --> 28:31.318
[suspenseful music]

28:36.366 --> 28:38.151
- Still scanning Metropolis,
General.

28:38.194 --> 28:39.761
- Find this kid now.

28:39.805 --> 28:44.418
[indistinct chatter on TV]

28:44.461 --> 28:46.463
- Nothing about Dad
on the news.

28:46.507 --> 28:49.031
- Can't find anything
on the Internet either.

28:51.947 --> 28:54.863
- Jordan you're n--you're not,
like, mad at me, are you?

28:56.822 --> 28:58.954
- Nah.

28:58.998 --> 29:01.609
I'm just a little tired
of being told what to do.

29:01.652 --> 29:03.176
That's all.

29:03.219 --> 29:04.830
- [scoffs] Yeah.
- [person cheering]

29:04.873 --> 29:08.398
[pounding on door]

29:08.442 --> 29:11.140
- Come on, man, open up.
- Oh, it's the boys.

29:11.184 --> 29:14.709
Ha! What's good, Mike?
What's good? What's good?

29:14.753 --> 29:16.058
- How you feeling, rock star?
Better?

29:16.102 --> 29:18.800
- I'm all right.
Yeah. Yeah.

29:18.844 --> 29:21.150
- Good. Let's go.
- Going where?

29:21.194 --> 29:23.065
- To pay some millennial
to get us a few sixers

29:23.109 --> 29:25.372
so we can celebrate properly.

29:25.415 --> 29:27.156
- That'd be--that'd be
tight, guys.

29:27.200 --> 29:30.203
But, honestly, my pops said
we got to stay here, so...

29:30.246 --> 29:31.247
- Oh, come on!
- He did.

29:31.291 --> 29:32.727
- All right.

29:32.771 --> 29:34.120
- It's not like
we're going clubbing.

29:34.163 --> 29:36.775
Liquor store's
just up the street.

29:38.559 --> 29:39.821
- You know what?
We won a big game.

29:39.865 --> 29:42.998
Come on. Let's go.
Come on.

29:43.042 --> 29:45.174
all: Yeah!

29:46.436 --> 29:48.656
- Whoo!
- You coming?

29:48.699 --> 29:50.397
- Yeah. All right.

29:54.705 --> 29:56.969
- What are you doing?

29:57.012 --> 29:58.274
- Get ready to run.

29:58.318 --> 30:01.321
[suspenseful music]

30:01.364 --> 30:07.022
♪

30:08.937 --> 30:10.069
Come on.

30:10.112 --> 30:17.032
♪

30:18.381 --> 30:20.819
[indistinct chatter]

30:20.862 --> 30:22.864
- Narrowing in
on his power signature.

30:22.908 --> 30:24.823
- Be ready to move.

30:24.866 --> 30:26.694
- I'm sorry about your head.
It's because of my power.

30:26.737 --> 30:29.566
It's hard to control.
- Tag, slow down.

30:29.610 --> 30:31.438
- I think it was caught
on camera.

30:31.481 --> 30:33.179
All I want is to just show you.

30:40.360 --> 30:42.841
See that flare?
It's coming from Jordan.

30:42.884 --> 30:45.713
I think he did...
something.

30:45.756 --> 30:48.063
That's what made me this way.

30:48.107 --> 30:50.326
it's crazy, Sarah,
but it's true.

30:50.370 --> 30:52.459
I had to tell someone I trust,
you know?

30:52.502 --> 30:56.158
Plus, you know him...

30:56.202 --> 31:00.075
and I wondered
if he told you something.

31:00.119 --> 31:01.947
Maybe you can help me.

31:01.990 --> 31:05.254
- I don't know anything.

31:05.298 --> 31:08.083
- Don't run.

31:08.127 --> 31:10.085
I'm here to help you.

31:11.478 --> 31:13.915
- Out there, boy. You got it.
You got. You got it.

31:13.959 --> 31:19.225
Oh! Hands like feet.
- There they are...

31:19.268 --> 31:22.184
the Crows.

31:22.228 --> 31:23.969
Hey, you look pretty good,
Jo-Jo,

31:24.012 --> 31:25.927
for a guy
who was dragged off the field.

31:25.971 --> 31:27.363
- Yo, Cutter.

31:27.407 --> 31:30.105
Seriously, man, come on.
Step off.

31:30.149 --> 31:33.413
- [scoffs] Oh, are you sore
about Eliza, Kent?

31:33.456 --> 31:34.893
Look, I know we used
to be friends,

31:34.936 --> 31:38.070
but I guess that's
over now, huh?

31:38.113 --> 31:39.810
- So what?

31:39.854 --> 31:42.204
You came here to talk
about how it feels to lose?

31:42.248 --> 31:44.076
- Wow.

31:44.119 --> 31:47.514
Look who found his voice.

31:47.557 --> 31:49.864
Dorky kid since forever.

31:49.908 --> 31:51.953
Cried if he was breathed on.

31:51.997 --> 31:53.824
[exhales sharply]

31:53.868 --> 31:56.827
What, now you're, like, the
best guy on the football team?

31:56.871 --> 31:59.526
You, uh, juicing
or something there, Jo-Jo?

31:59.569 --> 32:02.877
Is that what's going on?
You juicing Jo-Jo, huh?

32:02.921 --> 32:04.792
- Approaching
loading dock, sir.

32:04.835 --> 32:06.794
Suspect is dangerous.
Use whatever means necessary.

32:06.837 --> 32:08.274
- I need you both
to come with me.

32:08.317 --> 32:11.364
- No. No way.
You took me to that place.

32:11.407 --> 32:13.540
- I was only trying to help.
- They didn't help me.

32:13.583 --> 32:16.064
- Tag!
I give you my word--

32:16.108 --> 32:17.544
I will make sure
that you are safe

32:17.587 --> 32:18.980
and that you get
the answers that you want.

32:19.024 --> 32:20.590
But right now
we need to leave.

32:20.634 --> 32:24.246
The DOD is coming for you.
I need you to trust me.

32:25.813 --> 32:27.902
- On the ground now.
Do not move!

32:27.946 --> 32:30.078
- Bishop Six, stand down.

32:30.122 --> 32:31.514
- Oh, look at those eyes, man.

32:31.558 --> 32:32.994
Tell me the truth, Jo-Jo.
- Cutter.

32:33.038 --> 32:34.691
- Let him shut me up.
Right here, baby.

32:34.735 --> 32:36.606
- Cutter.
Jordan, Jordan, Jordan.

32:36.650 --> 32:38.086
Breathe. Relax. Relax.

32:38.130 --> 32:40.132
- On the ground now!
- We will fire!

32:40.175 --> 32:41.872
- No! Don't!

32:41.916 --> 32:44.136
Tag, stop.
- Engage.

32:44.179 --> 32:46.790
- You can't do this.
You can't do this.

32:48.923 --> 32:50.011
Oh!

32:50.055 --> 32:51.839
- Stop!
- Take him out!

32:51.882 --> 32:55.060
[dramatic music]

32:55.103 --> 33:01.631
♪

33:01.675 --> 33:03.198
- [groans]

33:03.242 --> 33:10.292
♪

33:16.603 --> 33:20.476
- [grunting]

33:20.520 --> 33:23.479
[suspenseful music]

33:23.523 --> 33:29.050
♪

33:29.094 --> 33:32.184
Aah!

33:32.227 --> 33:38.842
♪

33:44.196 --> 33:46.676
Stand down.

33:50.245 --> 33:53.248
- No. No.
He didn't try to hurt me.

33:53.292 --> 33:56.338
[indistinct chatter
over radio]

34:00.125 --> 34:02.257
- Those won't be necessary.

34:07.219 --> 34:10.091
You're not gonna be alone
anymore, okay?

34:10.135 --> 34:12.963
I promise.

34:15.531 --> 34:17.229
- I don't know what
you're upset about.

34:17.272 --> 34:19.144
The girl's safe
and on her way home.

34:19.187 --> 34:22.234
The subject's back in custody.
Let's take this as a win.

34:22.277 --> 34:24.410
- His name is Tag.

34:24.453 --> 34:26.368
- I wish I had your trust
in people, I really do.

34:26.412 --> 34:27.717
- So do I.

34:27.761 --> 34:30.111
- You put me
in a bad position tonight.

34:30.155 --> 34:31.939
- You know, I thought
about all the ways

34:31.982 --> 34:34.246
you might try
to stop that boy.

34:34.289 --> 34:37.727
Never occurred to me you would
actually use live rounds,

34:37.771 --> 34:39.773
let alone ones fitted
with Kryptonite.

34:46.171 --> 34:48.738
- My job is to protect
the American people

34:48.782 --> 34:50.697
by any means necessary.

34:52.699 --> 34:54.092
- And now I know.

34:57.007 --> 34:58.574
- Dad, Jon's hurt.

34:58.618 --> 35:00.402
- Superman.

35:01.751 --> 35:04.145
- Hey. Hey!

35:04.189 --> 35:07.148
Are we gonna talk about
what happened back there?

35:07.192 --> 35:09.019
- What's to talk about?
You saw what I saw.

35:09.063 --> 35:10.586
That's your story.

35:10.630 --> 35:12.371
- You are armed to the teeth
with the kind of weapons

35:12.414 --> 35:14.938
that would put you high
on the FBI's Most Wanted List.

35:14.982 --> 35:17.376
And this security badge--I sent
a photo to a friend of mine,

35:17.419 --> 35:19.160
and she said it's one
of the best forgeries

35:19.204 --> 35:20.596
she has ever seen.

35:20.640 --> 35:22.555
So why don't you tell me
who you really are

35:22.598 --> 35:24.252
and why you are in Smallville,

35:24.296 --> 35:27.081
'cause I don't buy
that you came to write a story.

35:28.691 --> 35:31.694
- I can't tell you why
I'm really here.

35:31.738 --> 35:33.348
But I can promise you,
like you,

35:33.392 --> 35:36.003
I am trying to prevent
something bad from happening.

35:36.046 --> 35:39.137
[cell phone ringing]

35:39.180 --> 35:41.791
- Hey, babe, can I call--

35:41.835 --> 35:44.316
How bad?
- I'm on my way.

35:44.359 --> 35:47.232
- Are you okay?
- To be continued.

35:51.149 --> 35:54.152
[engine turning over]

35:54.195 --> 35:58.721
- Doctor said the cast comes
off in six to eight weeks.

35:58.765 --> 36:01.202
- Could have been worse.
- Yeah.

36:01.246 --> 36:03.204
And he also said that "maybe"

36:03.248 --> 36:06.729
I get full range
of motion back, so...

36:06.773 --> 36:10.168
- Jon, I'm so sorry.
- Just--just shut up, please.

36:11.430 --> 36:15.521
- I--You know I never meant--
- Okay, but you did.

36:15.564 --> 36:17.044
You--you did, Jordan.

36:17.087 --> 36:18.524
You--you got emotional,

36:18.567 --> 36:20.308
and then I tried to step
in the middle of it

36:20.352 --> 36:23.181
like an idiot,
and now I have a broke-ass arm,

36:23.224 --> 36:26.314
and I'm probably never gonna
play quarterback again.

36:26.358 --> 36:28.360
So, thanks.

36:28.403 --> 36:30.188
Thanks a lot.

36:31.667 --> 36:34.453
[sighs]

36:34.496 --> 36:36.716
I'm going to bed.

36:39.675 --> 36:41.242
- You guys know

36:41.286 --> 36:42.983
that I would never mean to
actually hurt him.

36:43.026 --> 36:44.289
- Jordan. Jordan.
- Right?

36:44.332 --> 36:45.855
- That has nothing
to do with it.

36:45.899 --> 36:47.161
[door closes]
He's upset.

36:47.205 --> 36:48.771
And he has a right to be.

36:48.815 --> 36:51.296
I told you, your powers
come with responsibility,

36:51.339 --> 36:53.428
and I need you to get that.

36:53.472 --> 36:55.517
- Honey, we know
it was an accident.

36:55.561 --> 36:57.258
We know you're sorry.

36:57.302 --> 36:59.304
Jon knows, too.
He just needs a second.

36:59.347 --> 37:01.480
But your dad is right.
Things are different now.

37:01.523 --> 37:03.395
- Yeah, I know.
I know they're different.

37:03.438 --> 37:04.918
- Do you?

37:04.961 --> 37:07.399
Because you made a big point
at the hotel

37:07.442 --> 37:08.878
of saying you're different
from me.

37:08.922 --> 37:10.837
But you're not.

37:10.880 --> 37:13.579
That anger you felt that made
you want to use your powers

37:13.622 --> 37:17.235
the way you did tonight,
I have those feelings, too.

37:19.976 --> 37:22.631
- You do?
- Yes.

37:22.675 --> 37:24.633
But I keep them in check.

37:24.677 --> 37:27.114
Otherwise, I risk losing
the trust of the very people

37:27.157 --> 37:29.247
I've sworn to protect.

37:29.290 --> 37:31.597
When I first showed up
in Metropolis as Superman,

37:31.640 --> 37:33.686
there was a lot of talk
about what the world should do

37:33.729 --> 37:35.905
with someone
who had powers like mine.

37:35.949 --> 37:38.125
And it took me a minute
to realize that other people

37:38.168 --> 37:41.041
were more afraid
of what I could do than I was.

37:41.084 --> 37:42.695
So what I had to do,

37:42.738 --> 37:45.350
more than anything,
was earn their trust,

37:45.393 --> 37:47.395
prove to them that,
no matter what,

37:47.439 --> 37:49.963
I would never use my powers
to hurt them.

37:50.006 --> 37:52.879
20 years later,
every time I use my powers,

37:52.922 --> 37:55.142
that trust is tested,

37:55.185 --> 37:57.231
every time.

37:58.841 --> 38:00.800
Just today, in fact.

38:03.368 --> 38:05.718
The thing about trust,
Jordan--

38:05.761 --> 38:07.502
once you break it,

38:07.546 --> 38:10.897
it's take a lot longer
to heal than a wrist.

38:10.940 --> 38:13.943
- It's late.
Go get some sleep.

38:13.987 --> 38:15.902
We can talk about
this more tomorrow.

38:15.945 --> 38:18.905
[dramatic music]

38:18.948 --> 38:25.999
♪

38:27.348 --> 38:29.002
He's just confused.

38:29.045 --> 38:31.352
He's so young.
He's not ready for this.

38:31.396 --> 38:34.834
- I know.
Neither was I, but--

38:37.793 --> 38:39.534
- Probably not the best time
to tell you

38:39.578 --> 38:41.710
I almost got killed tonight.

38:41.754 --> 38:43.669
- What?
- I got into the mine,

38:43.712 --> 38:46.411
with the help of this supposed
journalist, Marcus Bridgewater,

38:46.454 --> 38:48.500
and he led me to something
called X-Kryptonite.

38:48.543 --> 38:51.154
Have you ever heard of that?
- X-Kry--No. No. Wait. Back up.

38:51.198 --> 38:52.939
What do you mean
you almost got killed?

38:52.982 --> 38:56.377
- Leslie Larr came after us.
Turns out she has powers, too.

38:56.421 --> 38:58.727
She tried to heat vision us,
and then Marcus zapped her

38:58.771 --> 39:01.251
with this,
like, high-tech ray gun.

39:01.295 --> 39:03.210
- Why? Why does a journalist
have a ray gun?

39:03.253 --> 39:06.387
That makes no sense.
- He's no journalist.

39:06.431 --> 39:09.825
I need to figure out who he is
and what he has on Morgan Edge.

39:17.442 --> 39:19.879
- Sarah, are you okay?

39:19.922 --> 39:23.273
- It's just crazy.

39:23.317 --> 39:25.188
I've known Tag my entire life,

39:25.232 --> 39:29.671
and now he has powers
or whatever.

39:30.890 --> 39:32.413
I was really scared.

39:32.457 --> 39:36.417
But I knew
that he would never hurt me.

39:36.461 --> 39:39.812
He was just
really confused, and...

39:39.855 --> 39:43.076
he was really
focused on you.

39:44.817 --> 39:49.474
He showed me this video
from the night of the bonfire.

39:49.517 --> 39:52.955
He had this whole theory
that whatever happened,

39:52.999 --> 39:57.046
whatever gave him his powers...

39:57.090 --> 39:59.309
had something to do with you.

40:02.095 --> 40:05.141
[zapping on phone]

40:08.101 --> 40:11.626
- I don't know
why he said that.

40:12.888 --> 40:14.847
- You know, even if--

40:14.890 --> 40:17.284
even if there was something,

40:17.327 --> 40:20.156
you could tell me, right?

40:20.200 --> 40:22.289
- Yeah, of course.

40:24.900 --> 40:26.902
- Okay.

40:26.946 --> 40:29.296
- How are you doing?
- [sighs]

40:29.339 --> 40:32.908
I just keep thinking
about what could have happened.

40:32.952 --> 40:36.085
Sarah told me that Tag...

40:36.129 --> 40:38.740
has these special abilities.

40:38.784 --> 40:40.394
He's not sure how he got them,

40:40.438 --> 40:44.616
but clearly this has something
to do with those mines.

40:44.659 --> 40:47.445
Lois, what aren't
you telling me?

40:48.924 --> 40:51.753
- I haven't put it
all together yet.

40:51.797 --> 40:55.365
But, yes, it does involve Tag
and two other people,

40:55.409 --> 40:59.108
both of whom have been linkedto Edge.

40:59.152 --> 41:02.677
He's up to something.
I just don't know exactly what.

41:04.026 --> 41:05.941
- I could help you figure out
if, in fact,

41:05.985 --> 41:08.683
he was up to something
dangerous or illegal.

41:08.727 --> 41:10.511
- Are you sure
you want to do that?

41:10.555 --> 41:12.295
He is very dangerous.

41:12.339 --> 41:16.256
- Look, if it's gonna keep him
from hurting other people, yes,

41:16.299 --> 41:17.779
I'm in.

41:17.823 --> 41:20.565
- And Kyle's okay with this?
- No. No.

41:20.608 --> 41:23.916
It's just best to keep this
between us for now.

41:25.178 --> 41:26.571
- Okay.

41:32.098 --> 41:34.927
I happen to know that we have

41:34.970 --> 41:37.146
a ton of rocky road
in the freezer,

41:37.190 --> 41:40.062
and I can't handle it
all by myself.

41:40.106 --> 41:41.542
- You think I'm six?

41:43.196 --> 41:45.372
- No.

41:45.415 --> 41:48.810
But I will say that I have,
as recently as this morning,

41:48.854 --> 41:51.857
kind of wished that you were.

41:53.946 --> 41:57.384
- I don't know how to fix this.

41:57.427 --> 42:00.605
I don't know what to do.

42:03.216 --> 42:05.392
I hurt Jon...

42:05.435 --> 42:06.524
bad.

42:10.702 --> 42:13.008
I can still hear
his bones snapping.

42:15.445 --> 42:17.578
He's my brother,
and I did that to him.

42:17.622 --> 42:20.581
- It was an accident.
- And Tag?

42:20.625 --> 42:22.365
That was
an accident, too, right?

42:22.409 --> 42:23.932
- It's not your fault.

42:23.976 --> 42:25.760
- Mom, I just had to look Sarah
in the eye,

42:25.804 --> 42:27.283
and all she wanted
was the truth,

42:27.327 --> 42:29.982
and I just had to lie
to her...

42:30.025 --> 42:32.637
to the one friend
I even have.

42:35.204 --> 42:37.511
You know, I-I think...

42:39.469 --> 42:42.124
I think some stupid part of me
actually thought

42:42.168 --> 42:43.996
that the powers would bring me
closer to people,

42:44.039 --> 42:46.433
but all they really do
is bring me farther away.

42:50.480 --> 42:52.265
- Come here, kid.

42:52.308 --> 42:54.528
- [crying]

42:54.572 --> 42:57.444
I just want it to end.

42:57.487 --> 43:00.490
- I know.
- [continues crying]

43:00.534 --> 43:04.103
[high-pitched ringing]

43:04.146 --> 43:06.192
- Jordan. Jordan.

43:06.235 --> 43:08.368
Clark! Clark!

43:08.411 --> 43:10.588
[Jordan grunting]

43:10.631 --> 43:12.720
- Jordan. Jordan.

43:12.764 --> 43:15.549
- [grunting]

43:15.593 --> 43:18.465
- I have to get him
to the fortress.

43:18.508 --> 43:21.468
[dramatic music]

43:21.511 --> 43:28.562
♪

43:51.716 --> 43:54.719
- Greg, move your head.
